&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Capital Projects Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 Hours&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Estates &amp; Facilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;West Bromwich&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post holder will be responsible for specific projects within the Estates Capital Programme across the Black Country Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust and will support the delivery of the Estates Strategy, Managing multi-stranded projects and ensuring that the physical environment matches the service strategic needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The direct management of Capital Projects Officers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assisting the Capital Planning and Property Manager and Head of Strategic Estates and Capital in Capital Planning and Property Management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note, Dudley and Walsall Mental Health Partnership NHS Trust and Black Country Partnership NHS Foundation Trust have merged together as one organisation to create Black Country Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust from 1st April 2020. Our aim as one trust is to provide sustainable, high quality, accessible and responsive services. Combining resources, strategies and talented workforce enables us to deliver a wider variety of outstanding services that are based on best practice and are continually improving. We are really excited by this opportunity and hope that you are too, we look forward to you expressing an interest in working joining us.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Previous applications will not be considered&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please Contact Sophie Wray&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07817 564007&lt;/p&gt;
